Chhāp tilak sab chīnī re mose nainā milāike
Bāt agam keh dīnī re mose nainā milāike
Prem bhakṭī kā madvā pilāike
Matvālī kar līnhī re mose nainā milāike
Gorī gorī baīyān, harī harī chuṛiyān
baīyān pakaṛ har līnhī re mose nainā milāike
Bal bal jāūn main tore rang rajvā
Apnī sī kar līnhī re mose nainā milāike
Khusro nijaam ke bal bal jaiye
Mohe suhāgan kīnhī re mose nainā milāike
Bāt adham keh dīnī re mose nainā milāike

You've taken away my looks, my identity, by just a glance.
By making me drink the wine from the love of devotion
You've intoxicated me by just a glance;
My fair, delicate wrists with green bangles in them,
Have been held tightly by you with just a glance.
I give my life to you, Oh my cloth-dyer,
You've dyed me in yourself, by just a glance.
I give my whole life to you Oh, Nijam,
You've made me your bride, by just a glance.

اگر کسی گانے کی روح نکالنی ہو تو اسے کوک سٹوڈیو میں گایا جائے۔
مجھے آج تک کوک سٹوڈیو نے متاثر نہیں کیا۔ بلکہ جب کبھی کسی اچھے گلوکار کے دھوکے میں کوک سٹوڈیو کے کسی کلپ پر کلک کر دیا تو اس گلوگار پر رحم آیا کر یہ کوک سٹوڈیو کے چکر میں کیسے آیا گیا۔ 
کوک سٹوڈیو اپنی اس مردہ موسیقی کو چھپانے کے لیے وڈیو کا سہارا لیتا ہے۔ تاکہ دیکھنے والے کی توجہ انتہائی فضول اور گانے کی دھن سے متضاد میوزک پر نہ جائے۔ 
عابدہ پروین، سجاد علی اور راحت فتح علی خان، ابرارالحق اور ان جیسے بڑے اور سنجیدہ گلوکاروں کو کوک سٹوڈیو سے پرہیز کرنا چاہیئے۔  کوک سٹوڈیو ان گلوکاروں کے اپنے اصلی اور سپر ہٹ گانوں کا بھی حشر کر دے گا۔
یہی وجہ ہے کہ کوک سٹوڈیو کا میوزک کبھی یو ٹیوب سے باہر نہیں نکل سکا۔

snippet.textDisplay:
The actual qawali/kalam Amir Khusro wrote is much longer with many different verses. As with many Sufi poems it's about immersing yourself in love, attaining union with the Beloved, the Divine. At one level it's about Khusro's love and devotion to his teacher Nizamuddin Auliya. Many of the lines are repeated, here';s a rough translation:

tan man dhan baaji laagi re
I’ve relinquished all I have – my wealth, my body, my very soul
dhan dhan more bhaag baaji laagi re
And good fortune has showered its blessings on me
laagi laagi sab kahen, laagi,laagi
Everyone  talks about and makes a pretence of devotion; Devotion, devotion
laagi lagi nah ang,laagi to jab jaaniye
But true devotion is not achieved until you know the true essence of devotion,
jab rahe guru ke sang,maula oi ji maula
When you devote yourself to your spiritual master, master o my master
khusro baaji prem ki
Khusro (Amir) plays the game of love
jo main kheli pi ke sang
If i play/pursue with the Beloved
jeet gayi to piya more
If i win I attain union with the beloved as One
jo main haari pi ke sang
If i lose i am still in his service
chhaap tilak sab chheen li re mose nainaan milaaike
You've taken away my looks, my identity, by just a glance.

snippet.textDisplay: Coke Studio Pakistan has brought together the musical instruments and talented players from all over the world with some singers I had not heard of before but the setup and this orchestra boosts their talent to the highest level. This is revolutionary and ingenious in the musical industry and will be instrumental bringing the world together to enjoy musical creations like these regardless of knowing the language of the song. Great creativity!
